I was wondering if you might
have some time this week

254
00:13:17.420 --> 00:13:20.646
to meet in person to... long-term work...

255
00:13:20.670 --> 00:13:22.646
ma'am. I'm sorry. Bad reception.

256
00:13:22.670 --> 00:13:24.710
Would you mind repeating
what you just said. ma'am?

257
00:13:28.010 --> 00:13:30.286
Are you there. Mr. Decker?

258
00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:32.616
Yeah. I'm here. I'm here. and I'm
very interested in meeting. Hello?

259
00:13:32.640 --> 00:13:34.366
Decker? Yeah. I'm here. I can hear you.

260
00:13:34.390 --> 00:13:36.536
Can you hear me? Ma'am?

261
00:13:36.560 --> 00:13:38.730
Ma'am?

262
00:13:49.200 --> 00:13:50.966
What can I say except it's pretty obvious

263
00:13:50.990 --> 00:13:53.216
there's a serial killer
loose in Fort Lauderdale.

264
00:13:53.240 --> 00:13:57.726
And maybe if the police hadn't
wasted so many resources on me

265
00:13:57.750 --> 00:13:59.396
after he killed Maya.

266
00:13:59.420 --> 00:14:00.900
they would have caught him back then.

267
00:14:37.750 --> 00:14:41.016
A sinkhole opened up outside
your window three weeks ago

268
00:14:41.040 --> 00:14:42.316
and you didn't come
to stay with us then?

269
00:14:42.340 --> 00:14:44.066
Hi. Catherine.

270
00:14:44.090 --> 00:14:46.090
You know you're the dumbest
ex-husband I ever had?

271
00:14:47.470 --> 00:14:49.276
Palmetto pastures. rj? Seriously?

272
00:14:49.300 --> 00:14:51.366
That's the best you can do?

273
00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:54.326
Well. the price is right.
cath. What can I say?

274
00:14:54.350 --> 00:14:55.696
If it's a money thing. you
know I don't mind helping.

275
00:14:55.720 --> 00:14:57.406
No. no. no. no. no. no. no. no. no. no.

276
00:14:57.430 --> 00:14:59.246
It's temporary. Just like me staying here.

277
00:14:59.270 --> 00:15:00.956
I'll be out of your hair in no time.

278
00:15:00.980 --> 00:15:02.190
You'll see.

279
00:15:09.030 --> 00:15:12.530
Great. It's great. Roomy.

280
00:15:14.950 --> 00:15:17.176
How'd your better half take the news?

281
00:15:17.200 --> 00:15:19.000
Said she wanted to talk to you.

282
00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:21.000
She's in the garage.

283
00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.856
You wanted to see me?

284
00:15:29.880 --> 00:15:31.010
One week.

285
00:15:32.390 --> 00:15:33.390
Beg pardon?

286
00:15:36.720 --> 00:15:39.786
You can stay here one
week. and then you go.

287
00:15:39.810 --> 00:15:41.746
Mel. if you think I want to
stay here longer than a week...

288
00:15:41.770 --> 00:15:44.560
one week. felon. Say it with me.

289
00:15:46.480 --> 00:15:47.480
One week.

290
00:15:49.780 --> 00:15:52.136
No. I won't talk to you
about Clay Gregory.

291
00:15:52.160 --> 00:15:53.386
No. no. no. no. no. no. I
was going to ask about Sofia.

292
00:15:53.410 --> 00:15:55.006
Yeah.

293
00:15:55.030 --> 00:15:57.136
She still draining threes like Steph curry?

294
00:15:57.160 --> 00:15:59.176
Like Sabrina ionescu.

295
00:15:59.200 --> 00:16:02.396
And asking about my kid
isn't gonna score you anything.

296
00:16:02.420 --> 00:16:04.896
Just the. the person

297
00:16:04.920 --> 00:16:07.066
who called the police about
the red BMW the other day...

298
00:16:07.090 --> 00:16:09.776
they interacted with the
guy who abandoned it.

299
00:16:09.800 --> 00:16:12.276
Said something. did
something. Am I right?

300
00:16:12.300 --> 00:16:13.720
I just want to know what they saw.

301
00:16:17.430 --> 00:16:20.286
Maya Gregory was your friend. I get it.

302
00:16:20.310 --> 00:16:22.956
But this case. it's about Rhoda Batista.

303
00:16:22.980 --> 00:16:25.456
and it's got enough eyes on it already.

304
00:16:25.480 --> 00:16:27.796
I don't also need some pretend p.I.

305
00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:30.376
Looking over my shoulder.

306
00:16:30.400 --> 00:16:32.216
let alone one flopping in my pool house.

307
00:16:32.240 --> 00:16:35.966
You know. I've started to
wonder if you don't like me

308
00:16:35.990 --> 00:16:37.806
because you're under the impression

309
00:16:37.830 --> 00:16:39.846
I might be the close-minded
type who'd be embarrassed.

310
00:16:39.870 --> 00:16:42.556
maybe even angry that his
ex-wife ended up marrying

311
00:16:42.580 --> 00:16:44.476
another woman.

312
00:16:44.500 --> 00:16:47.646
Hand to heart. Mel. it doesn't bother me.

313
00:16:47.670 --> 00:16:49.630
I knew cath was bi from day one.

314
00:16:51.340 --> 00:16:52.356
I mean. hell. we even entertained

315
00:16:52.380 --> 00:16:55.196
the occasional third party back then.

316
00:16:55.220 --> 00:16:56.866
I got work to do.

317
00:16:56.890 --> 00:16:58.530
Try not to get sent back to prison today.

318
00:17:02.180 --> 00:17:04.100
¿Intentas infringir El código?

319
00:17:05.480 --> 00:17:07.916
My Spanish is a little rusty.

320
00:17:07.940 --> 00:17:10.046
You didn't just happen to
confess to murdering two women.

321
00:17:10.070 --> 00:17:11.256
did you?

322
00:17:11.280 --> 00:17:13.416
Decker. What's it been?

323
00:17:13.440 --> 00:17:16.176
Two years? 18 months
with good behavior?

324
00:17:16.200 --> 00:17:19.386
You go to prison one time.
and suddenly it's all the jokes.

325
00:17:19.410 --> 00:17:20.926
I saw your ex's piece in
the herald this morning.

326
00:17:20.950 --> 00:17:22.976
Yeah? It's good stuff.

327
00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:24.686
It reminded me of the
way Maya used to write.

328
00:17:24.710 --> 00:17:26.346
All gas. no brakes.

329
00:17:26.370 --> 00:17:27.766
Yeah. Maya was something. wasn't she?

330
00:17:27.790 --> 00:17:29.356
Before she died...

331
00:17:29.380 --> 00:17:31.146
before you killed her. Before she died.

332
00:17:31.170 --> 00:17:34.316
you met me. what. once? Maybe twice.

333
00:17:34.340 --> 00:17:36.316
You hardly know me.

334
00:17:36.340 --> 00:17:38.156
So how can you be
so sure I killed Maya?

335
00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:39.696
Well. you were cheating on her.

336
00:17:39.720 --> 00:17:43.496
I was getting away with
it. So why kill my wife?

337
00:17:43.520 --> 00:17:44.746
This new murder. the one
from a couple of days ago...

338
00:17:44.770 --> 00:17:46.456
Rhoda Batista. That was her name.

339
00:17:46.480 --> 00:17:48.166
She was a teacher. She had
a mom. She had three sisters.

340
00:17:48.190 --> 00:17:50.036
Yeah. I'm sure you heard by now

341
00:17:50.060 --> 00:17:51.206
I was on an airplane when it happened.

342
00:17:51.230 --> 00:17:52.836
I didn't do it. I know you didn't.

343
00:17:52.860 --> 00:17:54.966
Then why are you here?

344
00:17:54.990 --> 00:17:56.876
Would I be right in assuming
that the insurance policy

345
00:17:56.900 --> 00:17:58.570
you had on Maya never paid out?

346
00:17:59.910 --> 00:18:01.716
Of course it didn't.

347
00:18:01.740 --> 00:18:03.716
Because the insurance company.

348
00:18:03.740 --> 00:18:04.806
like pretty much everyone
else in the state of Florida.

349
00:18:04.830 --> 00:18:06.846
knew you killed her.

350
00:18:06.870 --> 00:18:09.726
This new murder. though. I don't
know. maybe it changes things.

351
00:18:09.750 --> 00:18:12.646
Like you said. you were on
a plane when it happened.

352
00:18:12.670 --> 00:18:15.026
You think I hired someone?

353
00:18:15.050 --> 00:18:16.396
Told him to commit a
murder just like Maya's

354
00:18:16.420 --> 00:18:18.026
when I was at 40.000 feet?

355
00:18:18.050 --> 00:18:19.196
Yeah. police start thinking.

356
00:18:19.220 --> 00:18:20.197
"hey. maybe he didn't kill his wife."

357
00:18:20.221 --> 00:18:22.366
Then the insurance company.

358
00:18:22.390 --> 00:18:25.656
Suddenly you're. what.
six figures richer? Seven?

359
00:18:25.680 --> 00:18:28.036
This has been fun.
but I've got work to do.

360
00:18:28.060 --> 00:18:30.440
Me too. Clay. Me too.

361
00:18:40.700 --> 00:18:42.716
Decker investigations.

362
00:18:42.740 --> 00:18:45.386
Hi. I called last night. We got cut off.

363
00:18:45.410 --> 00:18:47.266
Hi. Yes. sorry about that.

364
00:18:47.290 --> 00:18:49.226
I would've called you back.
but your number was blocked.

365
00:18:49.250 --> 00:18:50.556
You're still up for meeting?

366
00:18:50.580 --> 00:18:52.396
Absolutely.

367
00:18:52.420 --> 00:18:53.267
Then how about we do it over a drink?

368
00:18:53.291 --> 00:18:55.436
You name the place.

369
00:18:55.460 --> 00:18:57.396
Ooh. Yeah. Do you know f.M. Station?

370
00:18:57.420 --> 00:18:59.236
I'll find it. See you at 7:00.

371
00:18:59.260 --> 00:19:00.640
7:00 works. but. can I...

372
00:19:02.350 --> 00:19:04.600
didn't get your name. Again.

373
00:19:10.480 --> 00:19:11.786
Yes?

374
00:19:11.810 --> 00:19:13.706
Hi. ma'am. My name's rj Decker.

375
00:19:13.730 --> 00:19:15.416
I'm a private investigator.

376
00:19:15.440 --> 00:19:16.506
I-I'd like to ask you a few questions

377
00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:17.990
about what happened yesterday.

378
00:19:20.070 --> 00:19:22.256
Me? Why me?

379
00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:24.346
Y-You're the one that
called the police. aren't you?

380
00:19:24.370 --> 00:19:26.266
You saw the person
who dumped the car.

381
00:19:26.290 --> 00:19:28.726
If I was. I don't think
the police would tell you.

382
00:19:28.750 --> 00:19:30.556
I knew it was you from the flower pot.

383
00:19:30.580 --> 00:19:32.726
¿Cómo? The one you
threw at the suspect.

384
00:19:32.750 --> 00:19:34.880
I saw little pieces of it on the ground.

385
00:19:36.840 --> 00:19:38.526
See. most of your neighbors.

386
00:19:38.550 --> 00:19:40.106
they like to use their
balconies for storage.

387
00:19:40.130 --> 00:19:42.656
You like to grow things.

388
00:19:42.680 --> 00:19:44.696
Yeah. you must have. what. a
couple dozen plants out there?

389
00:19:44.720 --> 00:19:46.946
So you saw the guy park.
and when he popped the trunk.

390
00:19:46.970 --> 00:19:48.326
you saw what he'd done.

391
00:19:48.350 --> 00:19:49.956
That's why he threw the pot at him.

392
00:19:49.980 --> 00:19:51.786
All I'm looking for is a description.

393
00:19:51.810 --> 00:19:54.210
I even brought you a few pots
to replace the ones you broke.

394
00:19:57.230 --> 00:19:58.506
The man was short.

395
00:19:58.530 --> 00:20:00.466
Maybe 5'2". Black.

396
00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:03.086
His back was turned.
so I didn't see his face.

397
00:20:03.110 --> 00:20:05.386
Just his terrible hat.

398
00:20:05.410 --> 00:20:07.096
What was so terrible about his hat?

399
00:20:07.120 --> 00:20:08.846
There was a penis on it.

400
00:20:08.870 --> 00:20:10.056
Penis? Did you say penis?

401
00:20:10.080 --> 00:20:11.306
Worse. An angry penis.

402
00:20:11.330 --> 00:20:13.266
And what made you
think the penis was angry?

403
00:20:13.290 --> 00:20:15.896
The face and the two
little arms flexed like this.

404
00:20:15.920 --> 00:20:17.106
Like it wanted to fight.

405
00:20:17.130 --> 00:20:19.000
Like this?

406
00:20:26.510 --> 00:20:29.496
Is this what you saw? Ay. dios mio. Yes.

407
00:20:29.520 --> 00:20:31.746
It's not what you think
it is. It's a jumbo shrimp.

408
00:20:31.770 --> 00:20:34.286
Specifically. it's the logo for
the Jacksonville jumbo shrimp.

409
00:20:34.310 --> 00:20:36.786
AAA affiliate to the Miami marlins.

410
00:20:36.810 --> 00:20:37.980
Does that help?

411
00:20:45.660 --> 00:20:46.870
I like your hat.

412
00:20:47.990 --> 00:20:49.200
Thanks.

413
00:20:52.290 --> 00:20:55.056
What? No. it's just I wish I
could have seen your face

414
00:20:55.080 --> 00:20:57.280
when you found that dead
lady in the trunk of that car.

415
00:20:58.670 --> 00:21:00.566
Darius.

416
00:21:00.590 --> 00:21:03.356
Hey. kid. deep breaths. deep breaths.

417
00:21:03.380 --> 00:21:05.020
No need to pull mom
into this. Come here.

418
00:21:09.470 --> 00:21:11.196
I didn't hurt that woman. okay?

419
00:21:11.220 --> 00:21:12.496
I'm not a killer.

420
00:21:12.520 --> 00:21:13.746
Well. given she had about six inches

421
00:21:13.770 --> 00:21:15.706
and 20 pounds on you. I tend to agree.

422
00:21:15.730 --> 00:21:17.876
The thing is. Darius. you are a car thief.

423
00:21:17.900 --> 00:21:19.246
And you did steal that beemer.

424
00:21:19.270 --> 00:21:21.206
You just didn't know the first person

425
00:21:21.230 --> 00:21:23.086
who drove it left the body behind.

426
00:21:23.110 --> 00:21:26.176
Who are you. man? What is this?

427
00:21:26.200 --> 00:21:28.176
Me? I'm a p.I. Yeah.

428
00:21:28.200 --> 00:21:30.966
As such. I do the occasional
job for an insurance company.

429
00:21:30.990 --> 00:21:32.806
That company insures cars.

430
00:21:32.830 --> 00:21:33.926
and so they keep
pretty meticulous records

431
00:21:33.950 --> 00:21:35.556
when it comes to car thieves.

432
00:21:35.580 --> 00:21:37.056
So I'm on a list. Yeah. you're on a list.

433
00:21:37.080 --> 00:21:38.556
That's how I found you.

434
00:21:38.580 --> 00:21:40.356
Someone saw the logo on your hat.

435
00:21:40.380 --> 00:21:41.776
So I checked the list for car thieves

436
00:21:41.800 --> 00:21:45.986
originally from Jacksonville.
and bam. there you were.

437
00:21:46.010 --> 00:21:48.486
Pinched last year for joyriding
in someone else's lambo.

438
00:21:48.510 --> 00:21:50.236
I'm a minor.

439
00:21:50.260 --> 00:21:52.326
All that stuff is supposed to be sealed.

440
00:21:52.350 --> 00:21:54.706
Yeah. well. hey. insurance
companies. what can I say?

441
00:21:54.730 --> 00:21:57.666
I tried to do the right thing. okay?

442
00:21:57.690 --> 00:22:00.746
I left the car trunk open so
somebody would see the lady.

443
00:22:00.770 --> 00:22:03.876
and the police would arrest
the person who owns the car.

444
00:22:03.900 --> 00:22:05.666
Well. the person who owns the car

445
00:22:05.690 --> 00:22:08.216
has an alibi described
by channel 7 as "ironclad."

446
00:22:08.240 --> 00:22:10.386
not to mention zero
connection to the victim.

447
00:22:10.410 --> 00:22:11.716
That's why I think the
car was actually stolen

448
00:22:11.740 --> 00:22:13.266
twice the other night.

449
00:22:13.290 --> 00:22:15.636
first by the killer and then by you.

450
00:22:15.660 --> 00:22:17.976
What I don't know. what nobody
knows except for you and him

451
00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:20.766
is where the car was abandoned first.

452
00:22:20.790 --> 00:22:23.300
Where did he leave it before you stole it?

453
00:22:29.430 --> 00:22:31.236
Hey. hey.

454
00:22:31.260 --> 00:22:33.616
Uncle rj! We're making ropa vieja.

455
00:22:33.640 --> 00:22:35.156
Wanna help? Actually. kiddo.

456
00:22:35.180 --> 00:22:37.616
I need a quick word with your mom.

457
00:22:37.640 --> 00:22:38.666
and then I have to go meet a client.

458
00:22:38.690 --> 00:22:40.076
Do you need to bring a gun?

459
00:22:40.100 --> 00:22:41.206
No. sweetie. I don't even own a gun.

460
00:22:41.230 --> 00:22:42.586
That's 'cause you can't own a gun.

461
00:22:42.610 --> 00:22:45.456
Can we just. please...

462
00:22:45.480 --> 00:22:49.466
So this guy stole the car
first. dumped it in the lot.

463
00:22:49.490 --> 00:22:51.756
and then the kid you
found stole it a second time?

464
00:22:51.780 --> 00:22:54.636
Yes. He's the one who ended
up in a car chase with police.

465
00:22:54.660 --> 00:22:56.386
But this guy. pop eye
calves. he's the one

466
00:22:56.410 --> 00:22:58.476
that killed Rhoda Batista.

467
00:22:58.500 --> 00:23:01.306
On orders from Clay Gregory
in order to clear his name.

468
00:23:01.330 --> 00:23:04.106
make a play for Maya's life
insurance money. or both.

469
00:23:04.130 --> 00:23:06.986
All I could get tonight was
video from a hardware store.

470
00:23:07.010 --> 00:23:09.066
But you canvass the area.

471
00:23:09.090 --> 00:23:10.316
maybe you find video
from a different business.

472
00:23:10.340 --> 00:23:12.236
catches popeye's face.

473
00:23:12.260 --> 00:23:14.140
We find him. he gives us Clay.

474
00:23:17.680 --> 00:23:18.890
Hey.

475
00:23:21.060 --> 00:23:23.286
Were you sleeping with Maya Gregory?

476
00:23:23.310 --> 00:23:26.296
I'm asking as a wife. not a cop.

477
00:23:26.320 --> 00:23:27.836
If it's something that's going to come out.

478
00:23:27.860 --> 00:23:29.876
I'd rather know now.

479
00:23:29.900 --> 00:23:33.596
No. I wasn't sleeping with Maya Gregory.

480
00:23:33.620 --> 00:23:35.506
The truth is. I didn't
even know her that well.

481
00:23:35.530 --> 00:23:38.636
She died. this person
you didn't know very well.

482
00:23:38.660 --> 00:23:40.476
and it was. what. one week later

483
00:23:40.500 --> 00:23:42.670
you lose it on some kid
who breaks into your car?

484
00:23:46.090 --> 00:23:48.396
A few years back. I'm
still working at the herald.

485
00:23:48.420 --> 00:23:50.026
City desk sends me out
on what they figured was

486
00:23:50.050 --> 00:23:52.616
a routine drug homicide.

487
00:23:52.640 --> 00:23:54.196
Someone smelled
something awful coming from

488
00:23:54.220 --> 00:23:56.286
the trunk of a car. called the cops.

489
00:23:56.310 --> 00:23:58.036
I show up just as
they're drilling the locks.

490
00:23:58.060 --> 00:24:00.140
Trunk pops open.

491
00:24:02.100 --> 00:24:03.746
I'm expecting the usual...

492
00:24:03.770 --> 00:24:07.376
gang banger. no ID.
multiple gunshot wounds.

493
00:24:07.400 --> 00:24:09.006
Not a woman with a hanger
wrapped around her neck

494
00:24:09.030 --> 00:24:10.320
and not someone I knew.

495
00:24:12.360 --> 00:24:15.370
Can you guess what I
did? Took her picture.

496
00:24:18.740 --> 00:24:21.556
I'm thinking. "hey. it's
Maya. It's Maya from work."

497
00:24:21.580 --> 00:24:23.436
But I just keep bracketing the shots.

498
00:24:23.460 --> 00:24:25.146
changing the angles
to get more of her hair.

499
00:24:25.170 --> 00:24:26.726
but not the face. not the face.

500
00:24:26.750 --> 00:24:28.356
No. the papers won't
print faces of the dead.

501
00:24:28.380 --> 00:24:29.936
That's policy.

502
00:24:29.960 --> 00:24:31.526
You were doing your job.

503
00:24:31.550 --> 00:24:33.906
Shoot everything.
That's what they expect.

504
00:24:33.930 --> 00:24:35.736
But 9 times out of 10.

